      "solution": "n = gets.to_i\n\nb = (2..).find do |b|\n    current = n\n    arr=[]\n    while current > 0\n        arr << current%b\n        current /= b \n    end\n    arr == arr.reverse\nend\n\np b",
      "statement": "given an integer [[n]] (in base 10), find the lowest base [[b]] such that [[n]] written in base [[b]] is a palindrome\n\nfor example with n=4:\n<<4>> in base <<2>> = <<100>>, not a palindrome\n <<4>> in base <<3>> = <<11>>, palindrome\n3 is the lowest base such that 4 in this base is a palindrome so the output should be <<3>>",
